l producing com\npanies as semi-speculative. Recent\nprice cuts should be of assistance in\nsecuring extension of the pro-ration\nagreements which expire on Feb. 1.\nRemington Rand Net $3.50 a Share\u2014\nBy Wall Street Journal.\n\u201cCalendar year earnings to exceed\n$6,000,000. January sales are good.\n$4 net indicated for year ending\nMarch 31.\u201d\nByers Production Costs Reduced\u2014By\nNewr York Telegram.\n\u201cReduced $5 a ton by use of Aston\nprocess for making wrought 1 iron\npipe. Greater saving anticipated for\n1930.\u201d\nTrade Revival Evidence Seen\u2014By\nBrookmirc Economic Sendee.\n\u201cWill be no continuation of the\nsharp recession of recent months and\nwe are confident of some improve\nment in present levels. The sooner\nbusiness reaches the bottom and\nturns up, the sooner the market will\nbe in a position to get under way for\na sustained advance.'\u201d\nPITTSBURGH LIVESTOCK.\nPITTSBURGH, Jan. 18.\u2014Hogs\u2014Re\nceipts, 1,200; market extremely active,\naround 20c higher; sows steady; 150\n230 lbs., $10.75 and $10.80; 260-300 lbs.,\n$10.25\u00ae 10.50; 100-130 lbs., $10.50\u00ae j\n10.75; sows, $8@8.60. Cattle\u2014Receipts,;\n50; market nominal. Calves\u2014Re- j\nceipts, 25 ;market 50c lower; few veal- j\ners, $13 @18. Sheep\u2014Receipts, 500;\nmarket steady; small lots fat lambs,\n$12(^14; strictly choice quotable1\nslightly higher.\nCLEVELAND LIVESTOCK\nCLEVELAND. Jan. 18.\u2014Hogs 300,;\nholdovers 212, steady to 15c or more j\nhigher, advance centering on stronger\nweight, bulk 250 lbs- down, $10.25,\nrough sows $8, stags $6.25. Cattle 25,\nquotable steady, week-end demand\nnarrow. Claves 10, quotable steady.\nSheep 150, quotable steady, $11.50\u00ae\n13.50 on medium to good kinds of\nfered, choice lambs absent*\nCOTTON MARKET.\nNEW YORK, Jan. 18.\u2014Cotton prices\ndeclined 6 to 11 points at the opening\nhere this morning on the exchange.\nJanuary opened at $17.14. March,\n$17.30, May $17.50, July $17.67, Oct.,\n$17.62, Dec., $17.71.\nCHICAGO COTTON.\nCHICAGO. Jan. 18.\u2014Cotton open- j\ned 3 to 8 points lower today; March i\n17 25, down 5; May 17.49, down 3;\nJuly 17.64, down 6; Oct. 17.62, down 8.1\nI\nComing Events\n\nJ\nBy Harris, TJpham and Co.\nTRADING FORECAST\u2014No impor\ntant chapge is expected in the char\nacter of today\u2019s market, with prices\nfluctuating within a narrow trading\nrange.\nAMERICAN CAN is meeting with\nvery good buying .and, subject to\nminor trading reactions, is likely to\ncontinue its upward trend. We would\nadd to holdings of \"AC\u201d on all minor\nsetbacks.\nPUBLIC SERVICE OF NEW JER\nSEY, as one of the leading Eastern\nutilities, affords an excellent oppor\ntunity to participate in the rapid\ngrowth of thys section of the country.\nThe company\u2019s earnings are con\ntinuing their strong upward trend\nand, over the long pull, \u201cPUB\u201d should\nsell very much higher.\nELECTRIC POWER AND LIGHT\n\u2014A new group is understood to have\nrecently become active in \"EL\u201d and\nshould have little difficulty in mark\ning the issue up several points. The\ncompany is affiliated with Electric\nBond and Share, and as a result a\nlarge part of \u201cEL\u201d has been taken out\nof the market. We would follow\nstrength and activity in the stock.\nFAMOUS LASKY\u2019S earnings for\n1929 were equal to $6.34 per share on\nthe average number of shares out\nstanding during the year, thereby\nshowing a gain of 78 per cent over\nthose of 1928 and establishing a new\nall time high record. Incidentally,\nthe rate of gain was more rapid as\nthe year progressed, last quarter re\nsults having been 111 per cent over\nthose of the corresponding quarter of\n1928. \u201cFP\u201d is cjieap at current levels\nand we recommend its accumulation\nfor substantially higher prices in the\nnear future.\nJOHNS MANVILLE is likely to\nmake substantial progress on the up\nside as soon as market conditions\nbecome more favorable. We would\nfollow strength and activity in\n\u201cJ